22/02/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The Central Elections Commission (CEC) announced on Monday (21 February) that political parties that owe debts to the CEC would not be allowed to receive campaign financing ahead of this year's parliamentary election. CEC specified that the measures would affect all formations that failed to pass the 2.5 per cent parliamentary threshold in the previous elections and did not return funds to the CEC as required by law.
In other news, Albanian and NATO officials met Monday to discuss the country's progress in adopting military reforms required to join the Alliance. Officials from the defence ministry briefed the NATO delegation on measures implemented last year and on priorities in 2005. (Albanian News - 22/02/05; AP -21/02/05)
